    "recap_headline": "Davidson College Athletics",
    "recap_text": "DAVIDSON \u2014 A six-run second inning and shutdown pitching led Davidson to a 10-0 seven-inning win over Lehigh\u00a0\u2014 and a series sweep \u2014 Sunday afternoon at Wilson Field.\nThe Wildcats, now 7-7, invoked the 10-run rule by scoring two runs in the seventh, including the clincher on\nForrest Lietz's\none-out RBI-single to right.\nIt sealed the first three-game series win of the season for the Wildcats, who also won both games against Fairfield (Feb. 20-21).\nJamie Daly's\nsecond home run of the season, a solo blast to right in the first inning, put the Wildcats on the right track before the second included Lietz and\nWill Brooks\ndriving in runs with triples and\nAnthony Torreso\nand\nMatt Manjooran\nsingling in runs. The Wildcats made it 8-0 in the fourth when Lietz (4-for-4) scored on a\nScotty Edwards\ngroundout to third.\nMeanwhile, right-hander\nEd Hall\ndelivered a five-inning, one-hit, four-strikeout performance in his first start of the season. Fellow senior\nBrycen Champey\ntook it from there, striking out three and allowing one hit in the final two frames.\nThe win is the 200th of head coach\nRucker Taylor\n's career. Now in his eighth season, Taylor's teams are 200-150 (.571).\nUp Next\nThe Wildcats will host Gardner-Webb Tuesday at 4 p.m. before opening the 10-series Atlantic 10 Conference schedule at home against Fordham\u00a0next weekend."
  },
